{"id": 3917, "date": "2018-08-19T05:00:06", "date_gmt": "2018-08-19T12:00:06", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=3917"}, "modified": "2022-12-28T06:17:52", "modified_gmt": "2022-12-28T14:17:52", "slug": "cover-me-helen-schneider-hearts-of-stone", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/08/19/cover-me-helen-schneider-hearts-of-stone/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me, Helen Schneider: Hearts of Stone"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Today&#8217;s cover is definitely on the obscure side&#8211;unless, perhaps, you live in Germany, where Helen Schneider was a popular recording artist in the late 1970s and early 1980s.</p>\n<p>Schneider may live and work in Germany, but she&#8217;s got New Jersey bonafides: she grew up in North Jersey, and her only American cinema credit was a memorable one&#8211;she played Joann Carlino in the classic\u00a0<em>Eddie and the Cruisers,\u00a0</em>which is pretty much a feature-length love note to the Jersey shore sound. (Never saw it? Go find it, and thank me later.)</p>\n<p>And then there&#8217;s her cover of Bruce&#8217;s &#8220;<a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2022/09/07/roll-of-the-dice-hearts-of-stone/\">Hearts of Stone</a>.&#8221; It&#8217;s not the most interesting of videos to watch (it was 1980, after all, still pre-MTV), but she certainly commits to the song.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Helen Schneider - Hearts of Stone 1980\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/suTLLHbZgT4?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Yes, that&#8217;s the actress who played Joann Carlino in Eddie and the Cruisers, taking a turn on Bruce&#8217;s torc